  "prompt": "How much time does it take to get a marriage certificate in India?",
  "response": "In India, the time taken to obtain a marriage certificate can vary depending on the state, type of marriage, and the specific office handling the application. Generally, the process can take anywhere from a few days to several weeks. \n\n1. **Hindu Marriage Act**: Under this act, after submitting the application, the marriage certificate is usually issued within 15 to 30 days, as the authorities may conduct a notice period for objections.\n\n2. **Special Marriage Act**: For marriages registered under this act, the process might take about 30 days as well, due to the required notice period.\n\n3. **Civil Registration**: If you are registering your marriage through the local registrar, it may take anywhere from 7 days to a month, depending on documentation and processing times.\n\nIt's important to ensure that you have all necessary documents ready, such as proof of marriage, identity proof, photographs, and any other documents required by the local marriage registrar to facilitate quicker processing. \n\nAlways check with the local authorities for specific timelines and requirements, as they may vary by region and specific circumstances.",
